Key Material Information Summary (Dart Mining NL - Triumph Drilling Update, ASX Announcement, 3 July 2025)

Exploration Results Highlights:

  • Drilling Completed: 1,906m (12 diamond drill holes) at Triumph Gold Project.
  • Assays Received: Results for 10 holes (New Constitution and South Constitution); 2 holes pending.
  • Significant Intercepts (Selected):
  • TRDD001A: 10.5m @ 2.63 g/t Au, 12.21 g/t Ag, 1.94% Zn (including 3.1m @ 7.42 g/t Au, 25.42 g/t Ag, 6.37% Zn).
  • TRDD003: 1.9m @ 4.36 g/t Au, 6.13 g/t Ag (including 0.4m @ 18.5 g/t Au, 25.6 g/t Ag).
  • TRDD009: 6.0m @ 1.57 g/t Au (including 0.4m @ 17.7 g/t Au, 44.9 g/t Ag).
  • New Mineralised Zones: 9 new lodes identified (8 of 10 holes), suggesting stacked mineralisation with potential resource upgrade.

Resource Implications:

  • Confirms strike continuity of existing 150koz Inferred Resource (March 2025).
  • Supports potential classification upgrade to Indicated Resources for economic studies.

Next Steps:

  • Drill testing depth extensions (up to 450m).
  • Exploration Target statement to be released in Q3 2025.
  • Open-pit development scenarios under review for near-surface high-grade zones.

Project Context:

  • Triumph hosts JORC Inferred Resource of 2.16Mt @ 2.17 g/t Au (150koz) at 1g/t cut-off.
  • 75% of resource within 100m depth; IRGS (Intrusion-Related Gold System) analogy to Ravenswood (5Moz+ endowment).

Actionable Insight: Results reinforce potential for resource growth and economic viability, with high-grade intercepts and new lodes likely to impact valuation positively.

• Exploration Program Initiation: Maiden exploration program to commence imminently at Horse Heaven Gold-Antimony-Silver-Tungsten Project (Idaho, USA), targeting high-priority drill sites.
  • Strategic Acquisition: Binding agreement to acquire Horse Heaven Project, with shareholder approval scheduled for 25 July 2025 (completion expected late July).
  • Key Targets: Focus on Golden Gate Fault Zone (3.5km strike, historical gold intercepts up to 71.6m @ 1.37 g/t Au) and Antimony Ridge Fault Zone (1.2km strike, surface samples up to 5.9 g/t Au, 19% Sb).
  • Drilling Timeline: Surface mapping/sampling in early July 2025; drilling planned to start August 2025 (pending permits).
  • Strategic Significance: U.S. has no domestic antimony production; project may address supply deficit. Engagement with U.S. government for potential funding/permitting support.
  • U.S. OTC Listing: Progressing, with updates expected soon.

Material Information Summary:

  • Drilling Results (Kpali Gold Project – Bundi Prospect, Ghana):
  • All five RC drill holes intersected gold mineralization (>1.00g/t Au), with notable intercepts:
    • 25BURC003: 18m at 1.22g/t Au (incl. 3m at 3.35g/t Au and 3m at 1.77g/t Au).
    • 25BURC004: 7m at 3.26g/t Au (incl. 5m at 4.34g/t Au and 2m at 9.46g/t Au).

  • Mineralization broadens with depth, confirming continuity along strike.

  • Exploration Upside:

  • High-resolution aeromagnetic data (acquired at no cost) to enhance targeting; auger drilling planned for early August 2025.

  • Follow-up RC drilling scheduled for Q3 2025 at Bundi and Kpali prospects.

  • Geological Context:

  • Orogenic gold style, analogous to West African Birimian deposits (e.g., 5.1Moz Namdini, 2.8Moz Black Volta).
  • Targets remain open along strike/depth.

• Key Points:
  • Ownership Retention: Raiden retains 100% ownership of the Mt Sholl Ni-Cu-PGE Project after First Quantum Minerals (FQM) withdraws from the MOU.
  • Financial Benefit: Raiden receives A$135k for unmet drilling commitments (Stage 1), totaling A$385k cash from FQM under the MOU.

  • Next Steps: Raiden evaluating development pathways, including regional opportunities, to maximize shareholder value.

Material Impact:
- Positive: No dilution from FQM earn-in; acquired data enhances project understanding at no cost.
- Neutral/Negative: Loss of potential partner may delay development funding.
